HEADWORD: Pentremites
<hw>Pen`tre*mi"tes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from
Gr. <?/ five + L. <ets>remus</ets> an oar.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A genus of crinoids belonging to the Blastoidea. They have five
petal-like ambulacra.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

